reviews.text:
Not a review of the station but for the walk from the castle along the railway and bay area to Plockton. 
Not too demanding though there are sections of foliage to navigate through and after heavy rain there are some muddy areas. You'll pass ruins of an old stone house which has a fairytale look.
Great views into the bay and you can reward yourself with some fish and chips when you get to Plockton.
